  var task_2_3 = "When your mind is in a state of anticipation and hope, it can be helpful to take some practical steps to ensure that your expectations are grounded in reality and that you are taking positive action towards achieving your goals.\n1)Set realistic expectations: While it's great to be optimistic and hopeful, it's important to set realistic expectations. Take a step back and assess your situation objectively. Ask yourself what is realistically possible given your current circumstances, and what steps you can take to move towards your goal.\n2)Focus on positive actions: Instead of just hoping for the best, take positive actions towards achieving your goal. Break down your goal into smaller, achievable steps and focus on taking action towards each one. This will give you a sense of control and progress, which will help alleviate any anxiety or stress you may be feeling.\n3)Practice mindfulness: Mindfulness can be a powerful tool for managing anticipatory anxiety. When you find yourself getting lost in thoughts of what could go wrong, bring yourself back to the present moment by focusing on your breath or your senses. This will help you stay grounded and centered.\n4)Take care of yourself: Self-care is essential when dealing with anticipatory anxiety. Make sure you're getting enough sleep, eating a healthy diet, and exercising regularly. These basic self-care practices can help you feel more calm and centered, which will help you better manage your anticipatory anxiety.\n5)Seek support: If your anticipatory anxiety is affecting your quality of life, it may be helpful to seek support from a mental health professional. They can help you develop coping strategies and provide you with tools to manage your anxiety more effectively.";


